<br>
Bitter snow, cold and sharp, blew under the cowl of his cloak, threatening to unglue the bushy mustache he had on his face. Thankfully, his fake beard was tucked beneath his heavy furs and was safe. Although of slim built, Ilsamore had managed to hide his size under mounds of furs and a few well placed mind-illusions completed the disguise. Anyone seeing him would have an image implanted in his mind, that of a burly norseman who's gruff appearance showed he was not to be bothered. At least Ilsamore hoped that his illusion would stick. He knew a bit of Midgardian, not enough to be fluent but enough to get by. That too, was a hope. <br>
<br>
A nagging voice in his mind told him this was folly, that venturing into an enemy realm, to find information on the whereabouts of his love's mother was foolish. He would surely get himself killed. And if the mids did not do it, the snow would be happy to oblige. As always Ilsamore shut out the voice and his legs plodded on. <br>
<br>
He was somewhere in the frontier lands, the snowstorm blurring everything more than ten feet away. He nearly cried out in surprise, breaking his disguise, when a form came out of the storm in front of him, large axe at the ready. <br>
<br>
&quot;What are yer about?&quot; The shape said. Ilsamore shielded his eyes from the storm and noticed it was a norseman, dressed in the uniform of a frontier guard captain. Just then, the winds died down for only a few seconds and he saw it. Like a wolf waiting to pounce on an easy kill; a large stone keep tucked between the rocky walls of a valley. This must be the frontier gate of the realm of Midgard, he thought. Thankful that the storm was helping him with his disguise and hoping his illusion would hold, he addressed the guard. <br>
<br>
&quot;bah git outta me way&quot; he grumbled in his best norseman voice. He was hoping to fool the guard with open confidence. Ilsamore wondered if the cold sweat he felt was due to the furs and the snow or his own nervousness. The guard bristled at his tone and narrowed his eyes. The guard took a step towards him, axe at the ready. Ilsamore thought his doom was at hand when the guard suddenly pushed him aside and stepped past him. <br>
Ilsamore blew a sigh of relief and trudged towards the keep gates without looking back. He heard the guard talking to a group of mids that had come up behind him. Thankful for the distraction, Ilsamore strode past a few more guards who were too busy shielding themselves from the storm than to check on travellers that had already been questioned by their captain. <br>
<br>
Ilsamore, a million plans forming in his mind and a million doubts to accompany them passed quickly under the gates of Svasud Faste and into the Wolf's Den. <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkelrycksdaocradioandroleplaycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vestachasiofra>VestachaSiofra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beloved lil Elf</span><br>  Posts: 72<br> <font color=#3333ff>(3/11/03 9:24:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fkelrycksdaocradioandroleplaycenterfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Into the Wolf's Den</span><hr size=1> Ilsamore managed to cross Svasud faste without incident. He found a road leading away from the keep and, having no other better plan decided to follow it. <br>
<br>
The storm eased up some time later, giving him a better view of the land around him. He could not deny the beauty of the land about him. The tall mountain peaks and snow-covered pines. But this was the realm of the enemy and every living being here would gladly slay him on sight. The elf plodded on in the waist deep snow for what seemed like days on end until he saw, up ahead in the dark of night the shimmering of lights. He must be approaching a village, he thought and made sure his disguise was still as it should be. A small sign outside the village marked the place as Hugginfell. He could make out a few huts set in a circle. Two troll guards stood lazily beside the entrance to the village and paid him no heed at all as he made his way in. The wind was still blowing, though it was finally relenting. The mentalist found what seemed to make up the village tavern and strode towards the door. If he was to get some information, this would be a good place to start. <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#A0B0E0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkelrycksdaocradioandroleplaycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vestachasiofra>VestachaSiofra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beloved lil Elf</span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#3333ff>(3/11/03 9:27:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fkelrycksdaocradioandroleplaycenterfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Into the Wolf's Den</span><hr size=1> Ilsamore pushed in the door to the tavern and had to use all of his strenght to close it back. But by then a large pile of snow had blown in and a good number of patrons, all grim faced and scowling, were staring at him. Ilsamore grumbled something about storms and waddled on towards the bar. The inn wasn't very full, but there were still about a half dozen mids there, four of them trolls who were already quite drunk and laughing heartily about some joke they had just shared. The other two, a dwarf and a norseman were picking up their game of cards that had been blown to the floor with Ilsamore's entry. Behind the bar, standing on a stool was a kobold. He glared a bit at Ilsamore but managed a smile when the elf dropped a small pouch of gold coins on the bar. <br>
&quot;What juse want?&quot; the kobold asked, reaching under the bar for a bottle of grog. Im fact, all he and was grog and any demand for something else was met with a scowl and a bottle of grog. Ilsamore merely grunted and accepted what the kobold gave him. Then, summoning up his courage, he tried to get some information out of the kobold. His disguise seemed to work and that bolstered his confidence. <br>
&quot;I wants some information&quot; the elf began. His heart skipped a beat when he forgot to say the &quot;for&quot; as &quot;fer&quot;, his accent evident to the now weary kobold who narrowed his eyes. But the blue creature did not press the point and only asked &quot;what kind infermation juse wants?&quot;. The kobold held out his hand, expectantly. Ilsamore sighed inwardly and fetched another pouch of gold. The kobold immediatly opened the pouch and dropped the coins in his hands, biting each one to test its make. &quot;I needs infermation on...&quot; Ilsamore panicked then, he could not remember the words he needed! <br>
&quot;On wha?&quot; the grimy kobold asked. <br>
&quot;infermation&quot; Ilsamore stated, trying to gain some time to think. <br>
&quot;Infermation on infermation?&quot; the kobold said and his frown was deeper now. <br>
&quot;Ggorolut&quot; Ilsamore blurted out. It was the name of the troll that had kidnapped Ilsamore's mother so many years ago. A name he had extracted out of the kobold slave the troll had kept and to whom he had given Tshaya as a pleasure slave. <br>
The kobold barkeep's eyes grew wide with fright. Ggorolut was obviously known to him and Ilsamore thought himself quite clever. <br>
That is until he noticed that the common room behind him was now very quiet... <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkelrycksdaocradioandroleplaycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vestachasiofra>VestachaSiofra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beloved lil Elf</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#3333ff>(3/11/03 9:28:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fkelrycksdaocradioandroleplaycenterfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Into the Wolf's Den</span><hr size=1> Ilsamore spun around, a spell already coming to mind. The four trolls were in front of him, faces locked in frowns of anger. The norseman and dwarf were on their feet as well, but giving the trolls ample room. <br>
&quot;What juse wants wit Ggorolut?&quot; the bigger of the trolls asked, the big club resting on hsi shoulder prompting a quick answer from the &quot;norseman&quot; dressed in think furs. <br>
Ilsamore's mind was racing to find a way out of this. He said the first thing that came to mind. <br>
&quot;Ggorolut's owin me and im lookin to get 'im to repay mes&quot; he said. His plan was becoming clearer now. He would find this Ggorolut, figure out a way to make him hand over Tshaya, or tell him where she was and all he would have to do then would be to walk out of the gates, the same way he had come in, with Siofra's mother in tow. <br>
He had not counted on Ggorolut being the troll in front of him though. <br>
&quot;Who are juse?&quot; the troll asked and reached to remove the furs covering Ilsamore. The elf, knowing that those furs were essential to his disguise tried to dodge out of the way, but the trolls flanking Ggorolut moved forward and grabbed him by the arms, pinning him to the bar. <br>
Ggorolut pulled off the furs, cancelling the mind spell and thus, removing the disguise. <br>
Ilsamore, determined to die honorable looked with defiance at the troll. <br>
The large monster's expression of surprise turned to one of rage and the last thing Ilsamore saw was a grey fist, easily as large as his head coming in fast. <br>
<br>
Everything went black and Ilsamore knew no more. <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#A0B0E0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkelrycksdaocradioandroleplaycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vestachasiofra>VestachaSiofra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beloved lil Elf</span><br>  Posts: 75<br> <font color=#3333ff>(3/11/03 9:29:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fkelrycksdaocradioandroleplaycenterfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Into the Wolf's Den</span><hr size=1> Every muscle in his body hurt. He was tied at the wrists with heavy shackles and hung from the ceiling of a large wooden hut. His left eye was swollen shut and he could barely see through the other. Blood oozed out of a large cut in his forehead and Ilsamore had to blink continuously to prevent the blood from covering his right eye. <br>
Then, of course, there was the cold. Ilsamore was naked from the waist up and his thin cloth pants did not stop the cold from freezing him to the marrow of his bones. He could no feel his legs but he considered that a blessing. <br>
There were three trolls in the room with him, including Ggorolut. They were talking among themselves in hushed tones, one of them occasionaly grinning his way. Ilsamore closed his eyes and thought of Siofra, hoping that the memories he had of her would manage to free him from his torment. Ilsamore closed his senses and let his mind wander to her. <br>
<br>
He could hear her soft voice, fell the warmth of her breath on his neck. <br>
<br>
That was when a large fist struck him hard in the belly, knocking the air out of him and bringing him sharply back to reality. <br>
<br>
The trolls, apparently having noticed that Ilsamore had found a way to escape their torment had rushed to him and started hammering him with their huge fists. <br>
The elf accepted blow after blow. He heard as much as felt some of his ribs crack and his jaw was dislocated when Ggorolut smacked with his forehead, both hands holding tightly to his shoulders. <br>
<br>
Until then he had managed to not cry out, to not give his captors the satisfaction of knowing they had broken him. <br>
<br>
But they the Ggorolut used a serrated hunting knife and carved his name in the frozen flesh of his thigh. <br>
<br>
Ilsamore screamed. <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkelrycksdaocradioandroleplaycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vestachasiofra>VestachaSiofra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beloved lil Elf</span><br>  Posts: 76<br> <font color=#3333ff>(3/11/03 9:30:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fkelrycksdaocradioandroleplaycenterfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Into the Wolf's Den</span><hr size=1> Blissfull uncousciousness followed soon after the troll at started his gruesome carving. <br>
<br>
But the trolls were not done with him. <br>
<br>
Cold liquid was splashed on Ilsamore. It smelled of urine. The elf tried to spit out some of the awful that had gotten into his mouth stuff but only managed a ragged cough. His &quot;good&quot; eye opened halfway and he looked at his tormentor, wondering what new torture the troll had devised and hoping that it would prove fatal. <br>
<br>
But the troll was not done with him. <br>
<br>
Ggorolut was accompanied by a norse woman, she looked even more cruel than the troll, a fact made even more obvious by the number of metal prods and knives she removed from a leather bag she carried. <br>
<br>
Ggorolut smiled from ear to ear and opened the cover from a brazier that stood before him. Red hot coals glowed within and the woman did not delay in putting her metal tools into those coals. <br>
<br>
Ilsamore looked at them with his good eye. Ggorolut apparently noticed the scrutiny and did not like it for he growled menacingly and approached him in two long strides. He slugged the elf in the eye and grinned at his own superiority. <br>
<br>
Ilsamore was able to open his eye just in time to see the woman come towards him with a long knife, its blade glowing red in the dim light of the hut. <br>
<br>
Ilsamore fainted. <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#A0B0E0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkelrycksdaocradioandroleplaycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vestachasiofra>VestachaSiofra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beloved lil Elf</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#3333ff>(3/13/03 7:28:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fkelrycksdaocradioandroleplaycenterfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Into the Wolf's Den</span><hr size=1> Siofra swallowed hard as she stepped through the fur covered doorway. It took a moment for her eyes to adjust to the gloomy interior after walking through the brightness of the snow. Uncontiously she hunched beneath her furs as Mogor towered above her. A scrawny, scarred kobold rushed forward upon seeing Siofra and Mogor enter.<br>
&quot;What juse want? Masta busy. No want visters.&quot; The kobold made shooing motions with its hands trying to usher them back out the door. Mogor just remained where he was looking at the kobold slave in distaste.<br>
&quot;Tells Ggorolut dat Mogor be here te see im.&quot;  The kobold was going to argue until it saw the look on Mogor's face. Quickly it rushed off to the adjoining room. As the kobold disappeared Mogor stepped forward so he was in front of Siofra. Her eyes took in the detail of the room and she shuddered. Axes and blades were displayed on all of the walls. Many still bore traces of dried blood. On one wall was a badly drawn and barely identifiable sketch of an elf., the throwing knives still stuck into it at odd angles. Mugs lay scattered about the tables and floor. The building stank of ale and death. <br>
<br>
The furs across the dorrway where the kobold disappeared opened and out stepped the biggest troll Siofra had ever seen.  He radiated brute force, his face set in a scowl.  Upon seeing Mogor, Ggorolut's face shifted slightly into what Siofra assumed was a smile. <br>
<br>
&quot;Mogor ole frend. Wha' juse doin here?&quot; Ggorolut stepped forward and clapped a large hand on Mogor's shoulder. <br>
<br>
&quot;And wha do we ave ere?&quot; Siofra started as a norsewoman seemingly appeared out of nowhere in front of her. Siofra thought the woman's beauty similar to the night. Beautiful and appealing in its own way yet full of hidden dangers. Mogor pulled on the rope that bound Siofra's hands so she stepped forward.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ello Eyverska. I's foun er when I was patrollin las eve. Tot juse mite like er. Juse got an eye fer da beauties after all.&quot;  Ggorolut's eyes roamed over Siofra.<br>
<br>
&quot;Aye, juse knows me well friend,&quot; he said sounding pleased.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well let's ave us a look ere, shall we?&quot; Eyverska said stepping closer to Siofra. Before Siofra could react the woman pulled the furs off her shoulders and down her arms, leaving them rumpled above her bound hands.  She looked Siofra up and down, her eyes glowing.  <br>
<br>
&quot;A gypsy ey? Wha a pleasan suprise,&quot; she purred. &quot;Yer nicely shaped too.&quot;<br>
<br>
With that one of the woman's hands shot out and clamped on one of Siofra's breasts.  Siofra gasped and her eyes went wide as she tried to step back. Eyverska's eyes narrowed and she stepped so close that Siofra could feel the woman's breath on her face. Eyverska reached up with her free hand and grabbed a handful of hair at the back of Siofra's head.  Thankfully Siofra's hair was weaved tight enough that her ears stayed hidden.  With a grin Eyverska pulled on Siofra's hair so that she was faced to look up at the norsewoman. <br>
<br>
&quot;Ye don' like dat ay? Well wha bout dis?&quot; With that Eyverska bent forward and planted her lips on Siofra's. Forcefully her tongue found its way into Siofra's mouth. As it was removed, Siofra clamped her teeth down on the woman's lip.  A hard fist across her face was her reward for her action. Siofra's green eyes met Eyverska's in defiance.<br>
<br>
&quot;Fiesty too,&quot; she said touching a finger to her bloodied lip. With a grin she turned to Ggorolut. &quot;Can I ave er m'lord? Teach er some manners fittin of yer house.&quot;<br>
<br>
Ggorolut watched the whole proceedings with an amused grin on his stoney face. <br>
<br>
&quot;Aye ye can ave er. Play nice wit yer new toy.  Bu first I wants te see er dance.&quot;<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkelrycksdaocradioandroleplaycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vestachasiofra>VestachaSiofra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beloved lil Elf</span><br>  Posts: 79<br> <font color=#3333ff>(3/13/03 7:30:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fkelrycksdaocradioandroleplaycenterfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Into the Wolf's Den</span><hr size=1> Eyverska went to reach for Siofra's bindings to untie them but Mogor was quicker than her. Siofra silently breathed a sigh of relief. It would do no good for them to realize she hadn't even been bound properly. Siofra rubbed her wrists as if easing away the pain from chafing ropes.   Eyverska Grabbed Siofra's hair once again and shoved her farther into the room.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ye heard wha Ggorolut said. Dance.&quot; Siofra took a few steps farther into the room and paled as Ggorolut's buddies came out of the adjoining room.  She forced herself to keep her eyes from going to Mogor.  She didn't know if he was going to stay or not.  Either way, he had done his job and if she got the chance she would thank him. <br>
<br>
