<br>
&quot;Now, now me pet. Dat's no way te look at yer mistress.&quot; Eyverska reached for the edge of Siofra's skirts. Siofra's whipped a foot out and she silently cheered in satisfaction as it met with the woman's chin. The blow barely phased the woman. Slowly a predatory grin crossed her face. &quot;Aye, I's gunna ave sum fun wit juse.&quot;<br>
<br>
Siofra had no way of knowing how much time had gone by as her body was used and abused.  Her clothing had been removed and thrown in a pile across the room. Luckily Eyverska had been in too much of a hurry and had not discovered the weapons and items hidden within the skirts and the tunic.  Siofra's mouth still tasted of blood from where she had bit her cheeks to prevent from crying out and her face burned from where she was hit more than once for less than satisfactory responses to her &quot;mistress's&quot; administrations. <br>
<br>
Now all was quiet. Eyverska lay on the bed snoring slightly, tired out from her &quot;lessons&quot;. Siofra moved her wrists around, feeling the heat of the rope burn on them. Throughout all that had happened Eyverska had left her tightly bound.  She shifted on the bed slightly to verify that the woman was really asleep. Satisfied that Eyverska wouldn't wake up Siofra began her escape.<br>
Gypsies were known for their skills at song and dance.  But they were also well known for their thievery and escapes. Siofra may have been stripped to nothing but she was not left without a weapon.  Turning her head to the side she tipped it back so it was within reach of her fingers. Carefully she pulled out the hairpiece that held her weaved hair in place. Her dark hair fell around her bare shoulders as the slim blade glinted in the faint light of the room. Slowly she worked the blade against the ropes binding her wrist. As soon as one was free she began working on the other.  Every muscle screamed at her each time she moved but she swallowed the pain and focused on her task. <br>
<br>
Finally the last of the ropes broke free.  To Siofra's horror one of the pieces fell onto the sleeping norsewoman. Eyverska rolled over, confusion marring her still sleep-filled features. Immediately Siofra was on top of her pinning her. She grabbed a pillow and quickly covered the woman's face to muffle any screams before she buried her small weapon in the woman's throat.  Siofra held the pillow in place until the thrashing stopped. Even then she remained where she was, listening for any movement within the house which signaled that the struggle had been heard.  After a time, when nothing was heard, Siofra rolled from the corpse and off the bed. She stumbled as she stood. Ignoring the pain and the blood which began to flow down her inner leg she made her way to where her clothing lay and dressed.  <br>
<br>
Cautiously she opened the door and stepped into the other room.  Ggorolut and his cronies still slept heavily, their snores filling the room. It was fortunate they had drank so much before passing out. Slowly she went around the room and stuck her blades within each throat as they slept.  Her one bit of satisfaction was seeing Ggorolut's eyes open and go wide upon seeing her blade above his throat.  The further shock on his face as her pointed ears came into sight When each of the beasts had been dealt with she slowly crossed to the door leading to the other room. Lifting the furs aside she looked in and had to fight down her stomachs urge to release its contents.<br>
<br>
Ilsamore hung from the ceiling, his body a bruised and bloody mess. In the dark it was hard to see the extent of his injuries but she knew it wasn't good. She rushed into the room and found where the ropes were secured. She cut the knot and slowly lowered his battered form to the floor.  Within a few steps she had his head cradled in her lap.<br>
<br>
&quot;Wake up Ilsa. I wouldn't let ye leave me last time what thinks I'm going te let you this time.&quot; She dug a hand within one of the pouches on her skirt and pulled out a couple of vials. Uncorking the lids she tilted Ilsamore's head back and forced him to swallow the contents.  She hoped the potions would be enough to sustain him til more help could be had.  <br>
<br>
She had to get the both of them out of the house. Looking around the room she caught sight of a sled. With some manuvering she managed to get Ilsamore on top of it before covering him with heavy furs which she found in the next room. <br>
<br>
&quot;Be right back Ilsa,&quot; she murmered quietly and ran to check a door she remembered seeing within the norsewoman's room. Sure enough it led outside. Siofra was pleased to note that it led directly out of town and there were no guards in sight. Quickly she ran back to where Ilsamore lay and grabbed the ropes on the sled. She was covered in sweat by the time she managed to get the sled outside. One it's tracks hit the snow it moved much easier.  Looking about she could only think of one place to go and hoped she remembered the way. She slipped on the carved ring Ayslyn had given her hoping there might be some way she could get Ilsamore the help he needed faster. <br>
<br>
Luckily the night had been clear with only a small amount of light from the moon.  Every so often she would stop the sled and backtrack a ways to hide the sleds tracks. It would do no good to lead anyone back to Ayslyn's people.  <br>
<br>
Morning had come and Siofra was still dragging the sled behind her.  She was passing by another small town when two squealing children caught her eye. She couldn't put her finger on it but there was something different about them. <br>
<br>
&quot;Vesta'chas!&quot; Siofra's head qhipped around at the familiar word. At the sound of the voice the two children ran squealing into a house.  Siofra heart beat loudly and she was torn by her curiosity but her concern for Ilsamore pushed her onward. <br>
<br>
Eventually she made it back to the old woman's house and passed out as she knocked on the door. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#A0B0E0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkelrycksdaocradioandroleplaycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vestachasiofra>VestachaSiofra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beloved lil Elf</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#3333ff>(3/15/03 7:44:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fkelrycksdaocradioandroleplaycenterfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Into the Wolf's Den</span><hr size=1> Large, cool hands roamed gently across her fevered skin, washing away pain, and unbearable heat. Siofra slowly opened her eyes. A firbolg sat at the side of her bed, his eyes closed in suplication. His hands wandered up and down her body, healing her wounds. His eyes fluttered several times before finaly opening. He let out a sigh, &quot;Thank you Spirits for your aid.&quot; He smiled, warmly down at her. &quot;Welcome back,&quot; his voice was rich and deep, and it seemed to roll through her. &quot;You made it back just in time.&quot; She noticed the wind roaring outside like an angry beast. The firbold nodded, &quot;One of their blizzards. Striking and beautiful to see, snug in a warm house, but I would not want to be caught in one. How are you feeling?&quot; <br>
