<br>
Siofra pulled the furs up to her chin and forced herself to remain laying down. She tried to sleep but each time she closed her eyes she saw Ilsamore's mangled form and Eyverska's evil grin. The reality of what had happened to Ilsamore and herself sunk in and she curled herself into a ball and began to shiver uncontrollably. She could still feel the warmth of the blood on her hands and remember the cold joy she felt each time she buried her blade within a new throat. <br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;Mogor left didn't he? He wasn't there?&quot; she asked the fibolg quietly.<br>
