<br>
&quot;Maybe ye'd better call upon that Slumbering Spirit,&quot; she said quietly. She heard him begin a soft chant. Turning pleading eyes on him she said, &quot;And please. Don't tell Ilsamore what happened if he wakes?&quot; <br>
<br>
The firbolg's eyes were unreadable as he nodded and Siofra drifted to sleep.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkelrycksdaocradioandroleplaycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vestachasiofra>VestachaSiofra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beloved lil Elf</span><br>  Posts: 83<br> <font color=#3333ff>(3/15/03 7:45:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fkelrycksdaocradioandroleplaycenterfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Into the Wolf's Den</span><hr size=1> Siofra slept through the rest of that day and well into the next. When she finally awoke it took her a while to remember where she was. Sitting up she let her eyes wander. Forcing down the thoughts that wanted to intrude she rose and looked for her clothing. Finding fresh clothing on a chair she quickly dressed and left her room. She had to find Ilsamore. <br>
<br>
She could hear voices outside the house and thougth she recognized them but none were the one she was hoping to hear. Ilsamore's room wasn't hard to find and she quickly stepped within the dark interior. <br>
<br>
Deja vu, she thought and moved to Ilsamore's bed. She couldn't help but cry as her eyes came to rest on his face. Most of the wounds had been healed but it was still slightly swollen and bruised. Blankets covered most of him so she couldn't see any of the other wounds. <br>
<br>
For the next three days Siofra never left his side. She wouldn't have even eaten anything if it weren't for the puncutal meals which were delivered to the room. <br>
<br>
