<br>
She was going to turn and enter the house but instead closed the door and began to make her way up the small hill. Stopping near a stup she noticed by the footprints that the other woman had been standing there for some time. A glint of light on the stump caught her eye. Reaching down she picked up a small jade sparrow. It still felt warm from the hand that held it last. <br>
