<br>
Siofra tried to push the thoughts aside as she paced the room like a caged lynx. Eventually sleep began to overcome her and she sat on the chair beside Ilsa's bed and rested her head on her arms.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkelrycksdaocradioandroleplaycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vestachasiofra>VestachaSiofra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beloved lil Elf</span><br>  Posts: 86<br> <font color=#3333ff>(4/6/03 4:23:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fkelrycksdaocradioandroleplaycenterfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Into the Wolf's Den</span><hr size=1> Slowly and with great effort Ilsamore managed to open his eyes. His right eye was still swollen but he could see with it. His eyes adjusted to the light in the room and his gaze quickly fell on Siofra, sitting on the chair besides the bed he was in. <br>
