Some of the wounds he received would stay with him throughout his life and they were not the ones that left scars. Ilsamore, despite his strong mental discipline, would need time to confront and accept those wounds.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#A0B0E0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkelrycksdaocradioandroleplaycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vestachasiofra>VestachaSiofra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beloved lil Elf</span><br>  Posts: 89<br> <font color=#3333ff>(4/6/03 4:29:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fkelrycksdaocradioandroleplaycenterfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Into the Wolf's Den</span><hr size=1> Siofra locked her fingers together and looked down at them. <br>
<br>
&quot;I was going te go to Midgard myself when I received yer message. Ayslyn had met up with me in Tir na Nog. He has friends and informants in Midgard. We're at one of their houses now.&quot; Siofra twisted her fingers together uneasily. &quot;They're all dead..... Those that hurt you....&quot;  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkelrycksdaocradioandroleplaycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vestachasiofra>VestachaSiofra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beloved lil Elf</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#3333ff>(4/6/03 4:31:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fkelrycksdaocradioandroleplaycenterfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Into the Wolf's Den</span><hr size=1> Ilsamore seemed to relax a bit more, as if some of his pain had simply flown away. He nodded but did not turn his head to see her. <br>
<br>
